    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-26T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-26T15:00:00-05:00" n="299"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d299">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/607</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-26T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>396. Legation 871, July 8, 7 p.m. Any agreements of the character referred to by
                    you should, so far as relates to the United States, be between the trade
                    association in question and the War Trade Board of the United States and signed
                    on behalf of the War Trade Board by the representative of the War Trade Board at
                    Christiania. Before agreements are actually signed, however, explicit authority
                    should be awaited. When agreements are in final form please advise as to what,
                    if any, modifications have been made in the drafts submitted to War Trade Board
                    by <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> in his
                    despatch of June 7, 1918.<note n="1" xml:id="d299fn1">See footnote 1, <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1188">p. 1188</ref>.</note>
                    Repeat to <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
